      <h2>Where it started</h2>
      <p>Half Fried began with a single question: why does Delhi's best street food have to come from a cart with no address? We set up in Lado Sarai with a proper kitchen, a serious wok station, and a menu that refused to do anything halfway.</p>

      <p>The name is cheeky, but the food isn't. Every momo is made in-house. The kurkure coating on our Kurkure Momos? We tested that for weeks. The chilli chicken sauce is a recipe we guard like it's classified information.</p>

      <h2>The philosophy</h2>
      <p>Fast food should be fast. It should also be good. We don't believe you have to sacrifice one for the other. Our kitchen runs tight, our portions are honest, and our prices stay within reach of everyone who lives in this city — students, office-goers, families, all of you.</p>

      <h2>Where we're going</h2>
      <p>We opened Lado Sarai. Then Mayur Vihar. Then Saket. Delhi keeps calling, and we keep answering. The menu grows slowly and carefully — we only add something when we're genuinely proud of it.</p>

      <p>Same mission at every location: make Delhi's favourite bite even better than you remembered.</p>
